'''Sankat Mochan Sangeet Samaroh''' is an annual music festival held at the [[Sankat Mochan Hanuman Temple]] in [[Varanasi]], [[India]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://thewire.in/the-arts/sankat-mochan-sangeet-samaroh-is-unlike-any-other-classical-music-festival-in-india |title=Why the Sankat Mochan Music Festival in Banaras is So Special - The Wire |last=Majumdar |first=Nandini |date=2016-05-08 |website=The Wire |access-date=2018-05-25}}</ref> It features performances in [[Indian classical music]] and [[Indian classical dance|dance]]. The festival is noted for allowing free entry to audiences, and for performers not charging any fees.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/music/echoes-from-the-temple-courtyard/article23512231.ece |title=Echoes from the temple courtyard |last=Khanna |first=Shailaja |date=2018-04-12 |website=The Hindu |access-date=2018-05-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.firstpost.com/living/varanasis-sankat-mochan-sangeet-samaroh-celebrates-the-city-and-the-indian-classical-music-tradition-4433607.html |title=Varanasi's Sankat Mochan Sangeet Samaroh celebrates the city, and the Indian classical music tradition - Firstpost |last=Ved |first=Nimesh |date=2018-04-18 |website=www.firstpost.com |access-date=2018-05-25}}</ref> It is scheduled every year to coincide with the Hindu religious festival of [[Hanuman Jayanti]] that celebrates the birth of [[Hanuman]], the presiding deity at the temple.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/sankat-mochan-sangeet-samaroh-an-ode-to-the-master-musician/article8504746.ece |title=An ode to the master musician |last=Khanna |first=Shailaja |date=2016-04-22 |work=The Hindu |access-date=2018-05-25}}</ref>

